# DrinkX CRM — production crontab example
#
# Drop these lines into the deploy user's crontab (`crontab -e`) on
# crm.drinkx.tech. They are NOT installed automatically — operator
# applies them by hand after reviewing paths and DATABASE_URL source.
#
# Sprint 2.4 G5 closes the soft-launch carryover from Sprint 1.5 by
# adding the daily pg_dump line below. The Celery beat scheduler
# already covers the application-level cron (daily plan, follow-up
# dispatcher, Gmail sync, daily digest); this file only contains
# system-level entries.

# ---- Environment ----------------------------------------------------------
# DATABASE_URL is read from /opt/drinkx-crm/infra/production/.env in the
# deploy host setup. Mirror it into the cron environment via the
# wrapper or with `EnvironmentFile=` if you switch to a systemd timer.
#
# Example using a tiny wrapper that sources the env file before the
# script — keeps DATABASE_URL out of crontab itself, where it would be
# world-readable to root.

# ---- Daily Postgres backup, 03:00 server time -----------------------------
# 0 3 * * * /bin/bash /opt/drinkx-crm/scripts/pg_dump_backup.sh >> /var/log/drinkx_backup.log 2>&1
0 3 * * * /bin/bash /opt/drinkx/scripts/pg_dump_backup.sh >> /var/log/drinkx_backup.log 2>&1

# ---- Notes ----------------------------------------------------------------
# - Logs append; rotate via /etc/logrotate.d/drinkx_backup if size grows.
# - Restore: gunzip + psql; full procedure in
#   docs/brain/06_OPERATING_PROTOCOL.md (TODO Sprint 2.5+).
# - All Celery-driven jobs (daily_plan_generator, gmail_incremental_sync,
#   followup_reminder_dispatcher, daily_email_digest) live in
#   apps/api/app/scheduled/celery_app.py — DO NOT add them here.
